    {
      "index": 0,
      "text": "set %a% = \u002210\u0022 as text",
      "lineNumber": 5,
      "indent": 0,
      "comment": "Cut 1 \u2014 cross-type antisymmetry. %a%=\u002210\u0022 (text), %b%=9 (number).\nif %a% \u003E %b% AND if %b% \u003C %a% must both fire (numeric, not lexical). \u00225\u0022 == 5 \u2192 true.\nProves rank \u002B coercion \u002B dispatch \u002B boundary; catches the antisymmetry bug rank exists to prevent.",
